OSI Model Layer has 7 layers as part of it
1. Application Layer
2. Presentation Layer
3. Session Layer
4. Transport Layer
5. Network Layer
6. DataLink Layer
7. Physical Layer

1. Application Layer
Any two applications inorder to exchange the data over the network has to define their own set of rules or messaging standards they should agreed upon in exchanging the data.
The server application defines the message structure and semantics in exchanging the data with client. The client application has to adhere/follow the rules laid by the server in communicating with the server application.

application protocols
http
smtp, pop3, imap
ftp


	


















